  "texts": [
    "For the Exchange Act violations, we modeled our jury instructions on (Martin 2013).",
    "The jury instructions each began with an introduction to securities laws and the claims in question.",
    "A series of five legal questions followed, each prefaced by relevant legal definitions and context.",
    "Each of the first four questions corresponds to one element of the charge that must be proven for the charge to be proven.",
    "The fifth question asked whether the juror answered the first four questions affirmatively (indicating a violation was proven)."
  ],
